Rollen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arragain>Arragain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 9:29 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pinning</span><hr size=1> Get shrunk, back into corner and f9 so your looking strait down on top of yourself, keep walking backwards, works for me <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Times New roman;font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Veteran Mymn&lt;Fires Within&gt;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Times New roman;font-size:large;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Barbarian War Machine</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haldainas>Haldainas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/02 12:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pinning</span><hr size=1> I usually look up at a 45 degree angle so I can see the top of the mob, as to see if I'm keeping good aggro, etc. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7808"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Haldainas/fullsize/Opt-Hald-Sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=parvvardt>Parv Vardt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/02 2:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pinning</span><hr size=1> Also for some fights where you can't reverse pin in a corner, you can pin alongside a wall.  This requires your raid to be smart about where they push (hi pets), and requires changing sides often to keep the mob in place.  You can also pin in a corner normally, but angle the direction the mob faces so that the back is free.  Be sure to talk with your rogues especially, they'll let you know when they get clean shots at the back.<br>
<br>
DMF/Lev helps me as well for reverse pinning. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66788">Parv Vardt</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | Halflink Overlord<br>
